and it's true for everybody.

00:28:16.180 --> 00:28:18.610
It's infinite possibility.

00:28:18.610 --> 00:28:20.380
It's like I don't
know what I'm going

00:28:20.380 --> 00:28:22.530
to do in the next
few minutes, but I

00:28:22.530 --> 00:28:24.310
feel I can get through it.

00:28:24.310 --> 00:28:27.690
It's an assertion
of a life force.

00:28:27.690 --> 00:28:31.160
"Star Wars" is primal,
and it is a fairy tale,

00:28:31.160 --> 00:28:33.640
but it's not just
a retelling of what

00:28:33.640 --> 00:28:35.830
Joseph Campbell had to say.

00:28:35.830 --> 00:28:39.730
It's real topic is the fork
in the road and the decision

00:28:39.730 --> 00:28:42.370
you make on the spot.

00:28:42.370 --> 00:28:45.000
It's universality
comes from its focus

00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:48.410
on the most essential feature
of the human condition,

00:28:48.410 --> 00:28:53.230
freedom of choice
amidst a clouded future.

00:28:53.230 --> 00:28:57.930
At the decisive moment, grown
children announce their choice.

00:28:57.930 --> 00:29:01.630
I am a Jedi like my
father before me.

00:29:01.630 --> 00:29:05.120
