And one of the nation's
leading newspapers

00:45:45.810 --> 00:45:48.365
described that judgment on
my part as unforgivable.

00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:54.780
That's reputational
pressure, big time.

00:45:54.780 --> 00:45:58.400
The internet can create
people who find themselves

00:45:58.400 --> 00:46:04.390
into groups of types, niches,
who are often linked tightly.

00:46:04.390 --> 00:46:05.840
And that will change.

00:46:05.840 --> 00:46:08.010
What I'm thinking is
fantastic in your question

00:46:08.010 --> 00:46:11.820
is in 1970s, because the
universe of communications

00:46:11.820 --> 00:46:14.120
options was so
much smaller, that

00:46:14.120 --> 00:46:18.220
to create an explosive network
effect, as "Star Wars" did,

00:46:18.220 --> 00:46:21.620
so it was everywhere,
a lot easier.

00:46:21.620 --> 00:46:25.220
On the other hand,
in nominal dollars,

00:46:25.220 --> 00:46:28.270
at least, "The Force
Awakens" beat "A New Hope."

00:46:28.270 --> 00:46:31.165
it didn't in real dollars, but
