about the movie is it,

00:54:45.750 --> 00:54:49.440
the Star Wars movies is they
move like a son of a bitch.

00:54:49.440 --> 00:54:53.070
And that's part of the
freshness, just this energy.

00:54:53.070 --> 00:54:55.960
And Lucas said, to spell
out a little bit what

00:54:55.960 --> 00:54:59.375
he loved-- not what he loved,
what he noticed in his movies,

00:54:59.375 --> 00:55:01.290
he said what defines
them is they have

00:55:01.290 --> 00:55:03.820
a kind of giddy exuberance.

00:55:03.820 --> 00:55:06.130
And he said that's very
surprising because I'm not

00:55:06.130 --> 00:55:08.280
at all like that as a person.

00:55:08.280 --> 00:55:12.880
And I've met him, and he's
a very present and intense

00:55:12.880 --> 00:55:13.570
person.

00:55:13.570 --> 00:55:14.290
He's not giddy.

00:55:17.300 --> 00:55:21.310
AUDIENCE: I definitely
agree with you on the, um,

00:55:21.310 --> 00:55:23.560
the second thing is it did
feel electric and it moved,

00:55:23.560 --> 00:55:24.576
you know.

00:55:24.576 --> 00:55:26.510
And that was the
other, like, going

00:55:26.510 --> 00:55:28.120
back to how I felt
about it as a kid,

00:55:28.120 --> 00:55:29.470
that was the other thing
that was a [INAUDIBLE].

00:55:29.470 --> 00:55:31.360
But like pulling
apart the themes

00:55:31.360 --> 00:55:34.170
for me and the
